    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1553.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 2, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I acknowledge the receipt of your despatch
                            of the 14th ultimo, No. 1046, relative to your proceedings in regard to
                            the correspondence with Earl Russell upon the subject of the Alabama and
                            other similar claims. Those proceedings are approved. An instruction of
                            the 27th ultimo, No. 1551, will more fully explain the views of the
                            department in the premises.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
